Package com.madrobot.util.collections

Set of java collection implementations like FastStack, FastHashmap, ExpiringMap, Pool etc.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Buffer
    Defines a collection that allows objects to be removed in some well-defined order.
    ExpirationListener<E>
    A listener for expired object events.
    Pool.Factory  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayStack
    An implementation of the Stack API that is based on an ArrayList instead of a Vector, so it is not synchronized to protect against multi-threaded access.
    CircularList
    Cyclic list implementation.
    CircularQueue<E>
    A unbounded circular queue based on array.
    CollectionUtils  
    ExpiringMap<K,V>
    A map with expiration.
    FastHashMap
    A customized implementation of java.util.HashMap designed to operate in a multithreaded environment where the large majority of method calls are read-only, instead of structural changes.
    FastStack
    An array-based stack implementation.
    MultiKey
    A MultiKey allows multiple map keys to be merged together.
    OrderRetainingMap  
    Pool
    A simple pool implementation.
    PresortedMap  
    PresortedSet  
    PrioritizedList
    List that allows items to be added with a priority that will affect the order in which they are later iterated over.
    QuickWriter  
    SimpleCircularList
    Circular list using a simple object array
    SoftHashMap<K,V>
    A SoftHashMap is a memory-constrained map that stores its values in SoftReferences.
    WeakCache
    A HashMap implementation with weak references values and by default for the key.
